Jeanette Chabalala, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Burgersfort &ndash; A dispute over soccer players may have resulted in the murder of a man, 44, who was shot in the Kgautswane village outside Burgersfort on Saturday, Limpopo police said.&nbsp;Officers&nbsp;have launched a manhunt for the gunman.&nbsp;The suspect, believed to be a well-known businessman, allegedly shot the&nbsp;victim several times, Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said on Sunday. &nbsp;"The motive behind this killing is still unknown but our preliminary investigations have revealed that they were having a conflict over soccer players... [they] both [have] soccer teams," he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The&nbsp;wounded man&nbsp;was&nbsp;rushed to the local clinic where he died on arrival. &nbsp;Ngoepe said the suspect left the scene in his vehicle, which was later found abandoned with flat tyres along the R36 outside Burgersfort.He urged residents not to try to arrest the man as it was believed he was still armed.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.